  "body": "Hi all,\r\n\r\nIn #4154 we implemented a custom HashTreeRoot for our beacon state data structure. A major optimization included in there is caching for fields such as `BlockRoots [8192][32]byte` and other arrays of Merkle roots. Unfortunately, the cache is seeing some collisions at runtime leading to problems in state transitions. This needs to be gated behind a feature flag to toggle it [here](https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/25b6aa0d33eaefd23da2655837c282cfe4a580a6/shared/stateutil/state_root.go#L27) and explorer further.",
